Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.48,0:00:14.30,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I have to make it through \Nthe evening party without
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.30,0:00:16.62,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Count Lawvine discovering my double identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.24,0:00:18.37,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.06,0:00:22.75,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I'd like to somehow find a way to get \NPrince Kyle to take this medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.75,0:00:25.38,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,If he doesn't receive treatment, \Nin the near future...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.38,0:00:28.72,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,his illness will keep him\Nfrom even being able to stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.18,0:00:39.66,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,What a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.58,0:00:44.27,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I thought that anyone caring for \Nan herb garden of this sort...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.27,0:00:48.45,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,must be someone in a profession \Nsimilar to mine, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.68,0:00:52.01,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Good evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.96,0:00:55.27,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,person who seems to be akin to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.61,0:01:00.18,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Professor Michel!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.02,0:02:50.78,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,What do you think of the aurora?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.43,0:02:53.41,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Has it given you a hint to your research?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.41,0:02:55.52,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes! Very much so!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.52,0:02:57.28,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,I'm glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:03:01.58,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Professor, asking you to \Ntravel all this way to bring me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.58,0:03:03.29,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Why are you apologizing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.82,0:03:06.29,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,You're my student,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.80,0:03:10.29,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,so whatever it is you want to \Nsee, I want to help you see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.67,0:03:13.24,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,If there's something you \Ndon't know, I'll teach you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.80,0:03:17.69,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Though, when you want to achieve something \Nsolely through your own efforts, I won't interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.22,0:03:26.43,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,In my third life, this man was my teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.33,0:03:31.99,Default,Kamil,0,0,0,,Pardon my insolence, but may I ask your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.38,0:03:36.57,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Oh, my apologies if I've startled you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.01,0:03:38.75,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I am Michel Hévin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.29,0:03:41.11,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I'm here from Coyolles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.88,0:03:43.66,Default,Kamil,0,0,0,,If you've lost your way,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.66,0:03:45.62,Default,Kamil,0,0,0,,we can escort you back to your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.62,0:03:47.38,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,How kind of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.38,0:03:49.29,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,But I'm not lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.82,0:03:52.14,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I'm interested in the young lady there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.78,0:03:54.03,Default,Kamil,0,0,0,,This individual is our empire's—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.03,0:03:55.36,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.92,0:04:01.55,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,My name is Rishe Irmgard Weitzner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.25,0:04:04.74,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Master Hévin, might you be a scholar?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.74,0:04:06.47,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,A scholar, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.47,0:04:09.22,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,That may be the simplest way to put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.88,0:04:12.23,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Your nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.56,0:04:14.60,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,You used sap from the \Ngelwood tree, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.10,0:04:17.48,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Though, it seems you've \Nused dyes to add color.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.98,0:04:22.08,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,What method did you use to harden it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.08,0:04:25.88,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I took lish grass and gibi \Nnectar, added labed leaf,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.88,0:04:27.99,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,and compounded them together with glue.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.99,0:04:31.62,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Did you refrain from using kirith \Nleaf in order to prevent air bubbles?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.62,0:04:34.00,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,You seem to know everything about it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.33,0:04:36.87,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,It's no more than a logic-based theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.12,0:04:41.01,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,What do you think would happen \Nif you mixed in some estoma sap?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.98,0:04:45.34,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I think it might harden even further.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:48.35,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Though, that's only a hypothesis, at most.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.35,0:04:51.27,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The actual results would \Nrequire verification.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.53,0:04:53.72,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,You're quite an admirable young lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.72,0:04:57.27,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,So admirable that were it possible, I \Nwould like to take you as my apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.30,0:05:02.20,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,If you wouldn't mind, just for the \Ntime that you're staying here,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.20,0:05:04.57,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,may I receive your \Ninstruction on various matters?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.57,0:05:06.82,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Yes. I don't mind at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.07,0:05:08.78,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.78,0:05:12.04,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Then, Master Hévin, this means \Nyou'll be like a professor to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.04,0:05:13.60,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,A professor, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.58,0:05:16.40,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,That sounds like fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.40,0:05:23.42,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I never imagined the day would come that \NI'd be able to call him "Professor" again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.99,0:05:29.86,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,By the way, my student,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:35.54,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,the herbs in this garden lie \Nslightly outside my expertise,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.54,0:05:37.44,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,so this is only a guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.26,0:05:43.19,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,but are you perhaps intending \Nto give Kyle some manner of medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.45,0:05:53.45,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe, I never imagined I'd have the \Ngood fortune of seeing you twice in one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.73,0:05:57.33,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Please, don't hold to formalities \Nfor my sake. Speak as you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.33,0:05:59.95,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Then, if I may take you at your word...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.46,0:06:04.92,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Michel, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:07.18,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I've found this amazing girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.18,0:06:09.14,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I thought you might want \Nto meet her, too, Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.14,0:06:12.79,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,This individual is His Highness, \Nthe crown prince's fiancée.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.79,0:06:14.80,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Really? Is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.25,0:06:18.40,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,But she's become my student, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.40,0:06:19.23,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.58,0:06:24.36,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,The herbal medicine she's compounded \Nseems like it would work for you, Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.36,0:06:25.65,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Herbal medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.12,0:06:31.37,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,It's outside my field, but I felt you \Nshould be used in this experiment, Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.37,0:06:35.74,Default,Riche,0,0,0,,Professor! You shouldn't use the \Nprince of a kingdom in an experiment!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.74,0:06:38.68,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Oh, have I made a blunder?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.68,0:06:41.33,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Common sense is such a \Ndifficult thing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.33,0:06:46.05,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,But I truly do, from the bottom of \Nmy heart, want Kyle to get well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.60,0:06:48.58,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.58,0:06:50.26,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.72,0:06:54.70,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,The greatest scholar in my kingdom \Nsays he wants me to try this medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.70,0:06:55.76,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,From the beginning...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.14,0:07:01.15,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I have been resolved to use any method \Nnecessary to cure this disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.10,0:07:05.98,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Then, I will prepare it immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.66,0:07:12.94,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.72,0:07:18.44,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The truth is that there is one \Nproblem with this medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.52,0:07:20.86,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Please, tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.79,0:07:24.38,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,This medicine...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.53,0:07:28.67,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,is incredibly revolting in flavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.13,0:07:30.90,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,The flavor is incredibly revolting?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.28,0:07:34.53,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Oh, is that all?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.53,0:07:36.46,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Kyle will be just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.46,0:07:38.95,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,After all, he's a very strong boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.95,0:07:40.80,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,He's earnest and hard-working, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.80,0:07:41.56,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.64,0:07:47.49,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe, if this is the ordeal \Nwhich has been bestowed upon me,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.49,0:07:50.19,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I need only face it down with \Nall of my strength and spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.70,0:07:54.07,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I know. I'll feed it to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.95,0:07:57.95,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor! You mustn't! At \Nleast ready some water first!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.20,0:07:57.12,top,Michel; background,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.12,0:07:57.95,top,Kyle,0,0,0,,Wait, I—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.15,0:08:06.04,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.49,0:08:09.91,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.71,0:08:12.84,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,So, Kyle, what does it taste like?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.84,0:08:14.23,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,What is the flavor like?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.59,0:08:18.35,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Bitter mixed with sour, and \Nmingled with the two...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.35,0:08:22.30,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,a particular stench, like that \Nof a horse stable, swoops in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.30,0:08:27.36,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Th-Then, after swallowing, a strange \Nsweetness wraps around the tongue like a slimy—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.36,0:08:29.66,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,There's no need to explain each stage!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.66,0:08:31.68,top,Michel,0,0,0,,Shall we try to get a clearer \Ngrasp of the flavor?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.66,0:08:32.11,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Excuse me! Please bring some water!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.68,0:08:32.11,top,Kyle,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.75,0:08:34.14,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Here. One more sip.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.14,0:08:35.37,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.80,0:08:47.66,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Now, my student, would you like to look \Nat this until your escort arrives?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.30,0:08:56.84,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor, this is—!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.84,0:08:59.11,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,My research records.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.57,0:09:01.28,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,They're too difficult for Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.28,0:09:04.23,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,He said that no one would \Nbe able to understand them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.76,0:09:11.49,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,You truly are a most intriguing girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.67,0:09:22.46,flashback italics,Michel; past,0,0,0,,Rishe, you truly hate \Nthis medicine, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.40,0:09:29.24,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,You're an intelligent girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.24,0:09:31.09,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,If you have a flaw,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.63,0:09:37.52,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,it might be that you only want to use your \Nknowledge and skills to make people happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.32,0:09:43.09,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,I think it's a mistake for you \Nto determine others' happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.56,0:09:47.52,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,If something is born into this world \Nas a poison, then its reason for being...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.52,0:09:51.52,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,would be to fulfill its role and bring \Nmisfortune to people, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.85,0:09:57.65,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,Is it truly impossible for a poison \Nto bring someone happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.32,0:10:02.08,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,The idea that someone is born \Nto bring misfortune to others...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.08,0:10:05.16,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,that preconception in itself \Nisn't like you, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.84,0:10:07.82,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,There's no need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.82,0:10:09.92,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,This compound hasn't been perfected yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.01,0:10:15.86,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,It's complete, but I've been unable to obtain\N the human resources necessary for testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.86,0:10:19.43,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Someone who will use this \Ncompound exactly as I wish...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.76,0:10:21.76,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Such a person doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.38,0:10:26.12,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,The professor and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.12,0:10:30.79,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,we just couldn't come to understand each \Nother when it came to that compound.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.48,0:10:35.72,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I wonder if the professor has met the \Nkind of person he was looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.95,0:10:39.86,Default,Dennis,0,0,0,,P-Pardon the intrusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.34,0:10:42.23,Default,Dennis,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe, your escort has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.37,0:10:44.21,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.86,0:10:46.66,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rishe, we're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.66,0:10:48.37,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.66,0:10:50.52,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness, why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.66,0:11:00.03,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,This is Michel Hévin, a scholar.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.03,0:11:01.77,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,He is incredibly knowledgeable
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.77,0:11:05.18,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,and he'll be teaching me all \Nsorts of things while he's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.61,0:11:09.12,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I am honored to receive such an introduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.12,0:11:12.84,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,I suppose I should present \Nmyself as well as possible here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.57,0:11:15.85,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Good evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.85,0:11:18.48,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,You're this empire's crown prince, I assume?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.36,0:11:23.44,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,It seems you've granted permission for \Nus to enter your imperial library.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.44,0:11:25.16,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.16,0:11:29.45,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,If you should require anything for your \Nexchange of knowledge with my future wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.45,0:11:31.16,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I will procure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.16,0:11:32.65,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Ask for whatever it may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.74,0:11:38.16,Default,Michel,0,0,0,,Then, I won't refrain from \Nmaking many requests of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.59,0:11:42.80,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Why did you suddenly come to escort me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.80,0:11:44.30,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I was on my way back anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.74,0:11:47.57,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Are you always out and about this late?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.57,0:11:49.68,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,When I become absorbed in my work,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.68,0:11:51.74,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I find myself forgetting the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.46,0:11:56.11,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Oh, but I slept until this afternoon, \Nso please don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.96,0:11:59.57,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.32,0:12:06.72,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Use that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.72,0:12:10.00,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,What? But this pocket watch \Nis such a precious item!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.00,0:12:13.63,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,It doesn't bother me. Since \Nit's easy to carry around,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.63,0:12:15.71,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I found it convenient to have for battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.71,0:12:19.59,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,By "battles," do you mean \Nin strategizing for battles?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.59,0:12:24.08,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Yes. There are some who doubt them \Nbecause they haven't existed for long,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.08,0:12:26.60,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,but it's just a tool which \Naccurately tells the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.50,0:12:31.02,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,His Highness's thinking is flexible \Nenough to adopt new technologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.78,0:12:36.27,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Someone who will use this \Ncompound exactly as I wish...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.85,0:12:38.83,flashback,Michel,0,0,0,,Such a person doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.63,0:12:44.70,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.70,0:12:46.00,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.43,0:12:49.97,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'll take you at your word and \Nindulge myself by borrowing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.97,0:12:55.08,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it, my master \Nin herbalism found these useful, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.08,0:12:56.64,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Your master?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.64,0:13:01.09,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes. A truly incredible \Nherbalist from Renhua.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.41,0:13:04.53,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,How does that man compare \Nto this master of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.53,0:13:07.84,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Professor Michel isn't an herbalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.84,0:13:11.58,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Though, he does use herbal medicines in \Nhis research, so he has the knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.58,0:13:13.85,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Then who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.23,0:13:19.41,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,He researches all the substances in \N the world and creates new substances.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.41,0:13:21.23,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,That's the sort of scholar he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.23,0:13:24.11,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,He creates new substances, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.11,0:13:29.37,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,In Professor Michel's case, he says that \Nhis objective isn't the creation of gold,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.37,0:13:33.47,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,but if we were to call him by the title \Nwhich most closely describes his work...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.69,0:13:38.15,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,it would be "alchemist."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.02,0:13:48.71,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,At tonight's party,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.71,0:13:53.63,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I have to act cleverly so that Count \NLawvine doesn't notice anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.62,0:13:56.52,Default,Elsie,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.93,0:13:58.71,Default,Elsie,0,0,0,,A letter has arrived for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.71,0:13:59.65,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.65,0:14:04.36,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Madame Mihaela.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.34,0:14:11.53,italics,Mihaela,0,0,0,,I said that the piece would \Ntake a month to complete,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.53,0:14:15.57,italics,Mihaela,0,0,0,,but I've made a request of an artisan \Nvisiting Galkhein from Coyolles,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.57,0:14:18.83,italics,Mihaela,0,0,0,,so it's likely that the date of \Ndelivery will be much sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.83,0:14:22.68,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Changing artisans makes \Nthis much of a difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.47,0:14:29.87,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,How beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.37,0:14:52.45,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.45,0:14:55.92,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The fact that you find\Nthis tedious is showing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.92,0:14:57.20,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I'm showing that on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.46,0:14:58.45,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,It isn't a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.66,0:15:00.90,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.88,0:15:06.03,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,For you to prepare an event \Nsuch as this for my sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.03,0:15:07.70,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I am entirely unworthy of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.18,0:15:12.09,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe, tonight you are \Nindescribably beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.39,0:15:13.91,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.32,0:15:16.85,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,How do you find you've \Nbeen feeling since then?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.21,0:15:19.98,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Thanks to you, I'm feeling much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.98,0:15:21.69,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,That's the most important thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.44,0:15:26.86,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold, I'm going to \Ngo and speak with the ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.19,0:15:30.30,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Prince Kyle, please do enjoy yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.28,0:15:38.06,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I've finished giving my greetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.06,0:15:40.64,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,so I've met my most basic obligations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.52,0:15:42.87,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,All that's left is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.75,0:15:49.52,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Now... focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.87,0:16:19.03,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I found him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.66,0:16:22.89,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,It's been a while, but that went very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.89,0:16:27.23,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I never imagined that experience from my fifth \Nlife would prove useful in a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.68,0:16:37.19,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I must keep my focus...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.18,0:16:42.89,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,and keep anyone from noticing \Nthat I'm avoiding Count Lawvine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.68,0:16:42.89,top,lady 1; background,0,0,0,,How are you, Lady Rishe?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.49,0:16:44.63,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.49,0:16:48.31,Default,Weilman,0,0,0,,I'm honored to meet you, Lady Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.31,0:16:53.68,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,No, the honor is mine. I'm very happy \Nto speak with you, Lord Weilman.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.16,0:16:58.58,Default,Weilman,0,0,0,,After hearing what happened from my mother, \NI've been looking forward to meeting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.58,0:17:01.20,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.20,0:17:05.46,Default,Weilman,0,0,0,,I heard that you were kind enough to \Nvisit my mother's shop the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.46,0:17:07.80,Default,nobleman 1,0,0,0,,He can't mean that that \Ndifficult proprietress...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.80,0:17:10.71,Default,noblewoman 2,0,0,0,,Even Her Majesty, the empress \Nwasn't accepted as a client.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.96,0:17:13.34,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Oh, could you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.78,0:17:18.47,flashback,Mihaela,0,0,0,,I'm the proprietor of this \Nstore, Mihaela Laure Weilman.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.74,0:17:21.85,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I merely picked out a stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.85,0:17:24.89,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,The one who sought to purchase \Nsomething there was Prince Arnold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.89,0:17:25.90,Default,noblewoman 1,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.90,0:17:28.52,Default,noblewoman 2,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold giving a woman jewelry?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.52,0:17:30.83,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I was surprised, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.88,0:17:36.82,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, I was informed that the \Ndelivery date will be much sooner than anticipated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.82,0:17:41.26,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,I understand that it's because an artisan \Nfrom Coyolles was entrusted with the work,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.26,0:17:43.41,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,but would that really make \Nthis great a difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.71,0:17:48.30,Default,Weilman,0,0,0,,Coyolles' jewelry artisans \Npossess superior techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.30,0:17:51.34,Default,Weilman,0,0,0,,The speed they can complete fine, \Ndetailed work at is completely different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.60,0:17:56.26,Default,Rishe,0,0,0,,Really? I suppose I should expect no less \Nfrom a country which produces gems and metals.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.80,0:18:01.49,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Count Lawvine seems to be standing still.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.72,0:18:11.23,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.23,0:18:15.40,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,please, will you lend Coyolles your strength?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.16,0:18:18.85,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Instead of aid through money or medical care,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.85,0:18:22.17,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,we would like to receive Galkhein's \Nsupport through military means.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.85,0:18:27.60,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,As you know, Coyolles' military \Nstrength is all but nonexistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.25,0:18:34.08,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Our kingdom is allowed to exist \Nbecause we provide gems and metals.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.17,0:18:38.16,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,If our neighboring nations so wished,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.16,0:18:40.51,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,they could destroy us at any \Ntime, and they threaten to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.67,0:18:43.89,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I want to extricate us from this situation
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.89,0:18:46.38,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,and obtain a method to protect our citizens!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.00,0:18:52.52,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,You're saying that Coyolles wants \Nto forge an alliance with Galkhein.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.52,0:18:54.07,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,It's just as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.29,0:19:00.05,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,I've been wondering what \Nyou were going to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.05,0:19:05.29,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,You pushed your disease-weakened body on \Nthat long journey to come here for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.48,0:19:11.83,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,The value of the existence of a royal family \Nlulled into naïvety by peace is questionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.00,0:19:16.38,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Even if, hypothetically, we \Nmoved this discussion forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.38,0:19:19.18,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,what does Coyolles intend \Nto bring to our empire?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.84,0:19:24.16,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,We will promise to give exports of gems and \Nmetals to your empire the highest priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.11,0:19:27.81,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Even if our kingdom makes \Nno profit whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.22,0:19:31.12,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,That won't work, Prince Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.12,0:19:33.74,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,You aren't suited to telling lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.65,0:19:35.89,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Don't make me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.29,0:19:41.32,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,If I were in your place, I would be sure to \Nattach a period of effectiveness to that offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.10,0:19:44.52,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,The gems which serve as the \Nkingdoms greatest source of funds
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.52,0:19:48.06,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,cannot continue to be supplied with \Nno regard to profit indefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.15,0:19:50.49,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.49,0:19:53.99,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's clear why you've come \Nhere with such a suggestion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.52,0:20:00.09,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Coyolles' mineral resources have \Nalready nearly run dry, haven't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.84,0:20:04.30,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.66,0:20:09.33,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,It's incomprehensible to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.93,0:20:12.75,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Your actions are nothing more \Nthan the actions of a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.80,0:20:21.02,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,My life... isn't likely to last much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.28,0:20:27.18,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,A new life is about to be \Nborn into my royal family!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.00,0:20:32.44,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,For the sake of that child's future, \Nand for the sake of our people...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.44,0:20:35.83,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,I must do whatever I can right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.84,0:20:41.15,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,From what I've researched, Prince \NArnold, you care for your people,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.15,0:20:43.91,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,and run a government which \Nextends a helping hand to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.54,0:20:45.51,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,If it were you, then—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.51,0:20:48.37,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,This isn't worth discussing any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.96,0:20:50.27,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Please wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.27,0:20:52.80,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Please, Prince Arnold!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.80,0:20:54.77,Default,Kyle,0,0,0,,Please help Coyolles!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.22,0:20:59.02,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,You seem to be mistaken about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.56,0:21:06.66,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rather than joining hands with another \Ncountry, invading and taking control of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.96,0:21:08.91,Default,Arnold,0,0,0,,that suits me much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.25,0:21:18.91,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Five years from now...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.29,0:21:23.47,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Prince Arnold will have become emperor \Nand will wage war on the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.47,0:21:26.33,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Coyolles will fight Galkhein.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.72,0:21:33.81,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,And so many lives will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.81,0:21:42.13,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,But Prince Kyle has confronted Prince \NArnold and proposed an alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.88,0:21:46.78,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,This is a branching point in history \Nwhich could change the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.62,0:21:52.49,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,Weitzner, I want to protect this kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.91,0:21:56.23,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,To accomplish that, I intend \Nto do whatever it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.68,0:22:01.77,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,As someone born into this, someone who has \Nlived beyond his time, I have duties to perform,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.68,0:22:04.44,flashback,Kyle,0,0,0,,and this is the greatest of them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.79,0:22:12.15,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Prince Kyle may be prepared for Coyolles
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.15,0:22:15.52,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,to become a vassal state to \NGalkhein if it means an alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.01,0:22:16.95,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:20.02,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,that would only change who \Nis in control of the nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.19,0:22:23.81,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Unless a relationship of \Nequal standing is created...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.70,0:22:29.90,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,But how?
